name: Hapsis
description: HAPSIS is an ancient Greek word meaning “joining” and is part of the root word for “synapse” the space between nerve cells. In this piece, I’m depicting nerves cells working in unison, almost like a dance, to carry out their electric work. HAPSIS is part of a series of imagined neurological events including SYNAPSE and AXON, also editioned on Hicetnunc. Created by Studio 3121 (Twitter: @Studio3121).
